description: From Latin expēnsīvus, from expendō; synchronically analyzable as expense +‎ -ive. In the sense of "high-priced" has largely displaced dear.

adjectives.description: expensive (comparative more expensive, superlative most expensive)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) Given to expending a lot of money; profligate, lavish.
Having a high price or cost.
(computing) Taking a lot of system time or resources.
examples: an unnecessarily expensive choice of algorithm
